    "causal_summary": "The FSRS retrievability number is SHIPPED and computed live on every read. `computeMemoryState` returns a per-memory `retrievability` plus a tier state (`tier-classifier.ts:325-328`), the inline power-law formula and the `calculateRetrievabilityScore` consumer both run today (`composite-scoring.ts:299,357`), and the tier thresholds are set (`tier-classifier.ts:39-41`, HOT at 0.80, WARM at 0.25, COLD at 0.05). Nothing reads that decayed number to flag a doc for a human refresh. A grep for `refresh_queue`, `freshness_queue`, or `auto.?refresh` across `mcp_server/` returns empty, so a doc that has decayed past COLD into DORMANT rots silently with no report-only maintenance signal.",
